WEBVTT

00:00:36.583 --> 00:00:38.375
Everyone, attack!

00:01:22.500 --> 00:01:26.875
<i>The cowardly past that I'd acknowledged</i>

00:01:27.208 --> 00:01:32.708
<i>Still not understanding why,</i>

00:01:33.042 --> 00:01:43.583
<i>I stand behind myself, scared</i>
<i>Projecting reality onto today</i>

00:01:43.917 --> 00:01:48.875
<i>I've drawn so many skies</i>

00:01:49.208 --> 00:01:53.583
<i>This must be my fleeting heart</i>

00:01:53.917 --> 00:01:56.292
<i>Out of control</i>

00:01:56.708 --> 00:02:02.000
<i>In my dreams, this body soars so high</i>

00:02:02.333 --> 00:02:07.125
<i>And it can brush away any fears that cling to me</i>

00:02:07.458 --> 00:02:13.625
<i>Asleep inside me, these budding</i>
<i>feelings start to expand</i>

00:02:13.958 --> 00:02:17.583
<i>I realize this, weak as I am...</i>
<i>As long as I had you</i>

00:02:17.917 --> 00:02:22.875
<i>I could stay strong in this dark world</i>

00:02:23.208 --> 00:02:28.833
<i>My heart will dream a long dream forever</i>

00:02:29.750 --> 00:02:32.208
<i>I want to always be with you</i>

00:02:32.542 --> 00:02:37.917
<i>I'll give you everything I have...</i>

00:02:41.125 --> 00:02:45.125
"The End of the World"

00:02:53.667 --> 00:02:55.583
How many did we lose?

00:03:01.958 --> 00:03:03.458
Fourteen died.

00:03:04.542 --> 00:03:05.708
No way.

00:03:08.708 --> 00:03:11.375
We still have 25 floors to go.

00:03:11.625 --> 00:03:15.875
Will we really be able
to reach the top?

00:03:40.125 --> 00:03:41.167
Kirito?

00:03:54.125 --> 00:03:56.042
Kirito, what are you...

00:04:05.208 --> 00:04:07.167
"Immortal Object"?

00:04:07.667 --> 00:04:10.208
Wh-What's going on, Commander?

00:04:11.125 --> 00:04:18.042
This man is protected by the system so
his HP will never fall into the yellow zone.

00:04:19.875 --> 00:04:24.250
Something has always bothered me,
ever since I arrived here.

00:04:25.542 --> 00:04:32.042
"Where is he hiding while he watches us
and regulates the world?"

00:04:32.583 --> 00:04:36.042
But I forgot a simple
piece of psychology.

00:04:36.375 --> 00:04:38.583
Something any kid knows.

00:04:38.917 --> 00:04:44.042
There's nothing as boring as watching
someone else play an RPG.

00:04:45.667 --> 00:04:47.792
Isn't that right, Akihiko Kayaba?

00:04:51.500 --> 00:04:55.417
Just for my reference, will you
tell me how you figured it out?

00:04:55.917 --> 00:04:59.417
The first time I thought something
was wrong was during the duel.

00:05:00.542 --> 00:05:04.667
In that last instant,
you were way too fast.

00:05:05.375 --> 00:05:09.833
I suspected as much.
That was an unfortunate mistake.

00:05:10.167 --> 00:05:15.458
You overpowered me to the point I needed
to engage the system's over-assist mode.

00:05:20.917 --> 00:05:23.500
Yes, I am Akihiko Kayaba.

00:05:23.500 --> 00:05:25.083
And if I may add,

00:05:25.083 --> 00:05:29.583
I'm the game's final boss, who would've
awaited you at the top floor.

00:05:33.458 --> 00:05:35.542
Not a classy move.

00:05:35.542 --> 00:05:39.083
The greatest player becomes
the most fearsome boss.

00:05:39.542 --> 00:05:41.792
Not a bad story line, is it?

00:05:42.958 --> 00:05:47.042
I always thought that you'd be
the one to stand before me at the end.

00:05:47.542 --> 00:05:53.708
Dual-wielding is the skill given to the player
with the fastest reaction time,

00:05:53.708 --> 00:05:58.208
and he was to be the hero
who opposes the demon king.

00:05:58.458 --> 00:06:02.875
But your power exceeded
my expectations.

00:06:02.875 --> 00:06:08.792
Well, these unexpected events are
what make an MMORPG so thrilling...

00:06:10.375 --> 00:06:13.417
Our loyalty... Our hope...

00:06:13.417 --> 00:06:15.208
How dare you... How dare you?

00:06:15.375 --> 00:06:17.750
How dare you!

00:06:23.208 --> 00:06:24.208
Paralysis?

00:06:27.333 --> 00:06:28.333
Kirito...

00:06:35.458 --> 00:06:37.417
What are you going to do?

00:06:37.417 --> 00:06:40.083
Kill us all and cover it up?

00:06:40.250 --> 00:06:43.708
Of course not. I would never
be as unreasonable as that.

00:06:44.417 --> 00:06:46.542
I no longer have a choice...

00:06:46.542 --> 00:06:52.083
I shall await you all on the top floor,
within the Ruby Palace.

00:06:52.500 --> 00:06:57.625
I've nurtured the Knights of the Blood Oath
and other front-line players,

00:06:57.625 --> 00:07:00.208
so it's a shame to
leave them partway.

00:07:00.208 --> 00:07:04.292
However, I'm sure that with your power,
you'll reach me eventually.

00:07:04.583 --> 00:07:06.333
But before that...

00:07:07.542 --> 00:07:12.792
Kirito, I must reward you
for discerning my identity.

00:07:13.250 --> 00:07:15.917
--I shall give you a chance.
--A chance?

00:07:15.917 --> 00:07:19.542
The chance to fight me one-on-one.

00:07:19.750 --> 00:07:22.708
Needless to say, I'll deactivate
my immortal status.

00:07:22.958 --> 00:07:29.167
Defeat me and the game will be cleared.
And all the players will be able to log out.

00:07:29.167 --> 00:07:30.208
What do you say?

00:07:31.792 --> 00:07:33.333
Don't do it, Kirito!

00:07:33.333 --> 00:07:35.542
For now... For now,
we should fall back.

00:08:05.917 --> 00:08:06.917
Quit playing around.

00:08:08.583 --> 00:08:11.333
You're on. Let's finish this.

00:08:11.333 --> 00:08:12.583
Kirito!

00:08:12.917 --> 00:08:16.208
I'm sorry. But this is something
I can't run away from.

00:08:17.708 --> 00:08:20.542
You're not planning to die, are you?

00:08:20.792 --> 00:08:22.958
No, I'm going to win.

00:08:23.375 --> 00:08:25.583
I'll win and end this world.

00:08:25.583 --> 00:08:26.667
All right.

00:08:27.042 --> 00:08:29.458
I believe in you, Kirito.

00:08:41.750 --> 00:08:42.875
Kirito!

00:08:45.667 --> 00:08:46.667
Agil...

00:08:48.083 --> 00:08:51.875
Thanks for supporting the
swordsman class all this time.

00:08:52.792 --> 00:08:56.500
I knew all about it... That you
spent most of your earnings

00:08:56.500 --> 00:08:59.958
helping the middle-zone
players to improve.

00:09:02.083 --> 00:09:03.083
Klein...

00:09:04.875 --> 00:09:07.042
I really am sorry

00:09:08.250 --> 00:09:10.042
for leaving you behind that day.

00:09:10.833 --> 00:09:13.042
D-Damn it, Kirito!

00:09:13.500 --> 00:09:17.208
Don't you apologize!
Don't you dare apologize to me now!

00:09:17.458 --> 00:09:19.042
I won't forgive you...

00:09:19.042 --> 00:09:24.292
I swear I won't forgive you until you
buy me a meal on the other side!

00:09:24.500 --> 00:09:25.500
Got it.

00:09:26.083 --> 00:09:27.542
See you on the other side.

00:09:35.208 --> 00:09:38.042
If you don't mind,
I have one request.

00:09:38.333 --> 00:09:39.583
What is it?

00:09:39.583 --> 00:09:41.792
I don't plan to go down easily.

00:09:42.208 --> 00:09:43.625
But if I die here...

00:09:44.333 --> 00:09:48.500
For a while at least... I want you to
make sure that Asuna can't kill herself.

00:09:50.625 --> 00:09:51.958
Very well.

00:09:52.167 --> 00:09:54.167
Kirito, no!

00:09:54.167 --> 00:09:57.542
That's not... That's not fair!

00:10:05.833 --> 00:10:07.542
Kirito!

00:10:08.500 --> 00:10:12.583
<i>This isn't a duel... It's simply</i>
<i>a fight to the death.</i>

00:10:13.167 --> 00:10:17.500
<i>That's right. I'm going to kill this man!</i>

00:10:27.375 --> 00:10:30.167
<i>He's the one who designed</i>
<i>the dual-wielding skill.</i>

00:10:30.167 --> 00:10:34.000
<i>He'll be able to block all of the</i>
<i>pre-programmed combos.</i>

00:10:34.417 --> 00:10:39.000
<i>I have to defeat him with my own power,</i>
<i>without using the sword skills!</i>

00:10:40.125 --> 00:10:41.125
<i>Faster!</i>

00:10:41.708 --> 00:10:43.458
<i>I have to go faster!</i>

00:11:14.833 --> 00:11:16.375
<i>I'm sorry, Asuna...</i>

00:11:17.000 --> 00:11:18.875
<i>I want you at least to live.</i>

00:11:29.458 --> 00:11:31.875
Farewell, Kirito.

00:11:56.875 --> 00:11:59.583
You're kidding, right? Asuna...

00:11:59.583 --> 00:12:02.250
This can't... This can't be...

00:12:07.417 --> 00:12:08.417
I'm sorry.

00:12:10.708 --> 00:12:12.000
Goodbye.

00:12:32.375 --> 00:12:34.167
That was a surprise.

00:12:34.458 --> 00:12:38.417
I don't believe I programmed a way
to neutralize paralysis on your own.

00:12:39.167 --> 00:12:41.625
I guess these things happen sometimes.

00:13:33.000 --> 00:13:35.208
<i>It's over now...</i>

00:13:39.458 --> 00:13:41.792
I believe in you, Kirito.

00:13:57.917 --> 00:13:59.125
Not yet...

00:14:06.625 --> 00:14:07.875
Not yet!

00:14:31.667 --> 00:14:34.458
<i>Is this good enough?</i>

00:15:08.917 --> 00:15:11.667
<i>As of 2:55 PM, November 7,</i>

00:15:12.458 --> 00:15:14.583
<i>the game has been cleared.</i>

00:15:15.125 --> 00:15:17.292
<i>The game has been cleared.</i>

00:15:33.583 --> 00:15:35.000
Where am I?

00:15:39.542 --> 00:15:42.583
"Initiating Final Phase"

00:15:46.083 --> 00:15:47.125
Kirito?

00:16:03.208 --> 00:16:06.250
Sorry. I ended up dying too.

00:16:07.167 --> 00:16:08.250
Dummy...

00:16:24.292 --> 00:16:26.917
I wonder where we are?

00:16:41.417 --> 00:16:43.333
Quite a view, isn't it?

00:16:52.708 --> 00:16:54.542
Akihiko Kayaba...

00:16:55.000 --> 00:17:01.417
The SAO mainframe, located in
the fifth-level basement at Argus HQ,

00:17:01.417 --> 00:17:04.250
is deleting all data on
its storage devices.

00:17:05.292 --> 00:17:10.208
In 10 minutes or so, everything
in this world will vanish.

00:17:10.917 --> 00:17:13.917
What's happened to
the people down there?

00:17:15.167 --> 00:17:17.167
You needn't worry about them.

00:17:17.167 --> 00:17:24.083
Just a moment ago, the remaining
6,147 players were logged out.

00:17:25.625 --> 00:17:27.542
And the ones who died?

00:17:27.542 --> 00:17:30.542
What about the 4,000 people who died?

00:17:31.167 --> 00:17:33.333
Their minds will never return.

00:17:33.667 --> 00:17:37.458
The dead vanish from our midst...
It's the same in any world.

00:17:40.125 --> 00:17:41.500
Why...

00:17:41.750 --> 00:17:44.208
Why did you do this?

00:17:44.208 --> 00:17:46.083
Why, you ask?

00:17:47.208 --> 00:17:49.917
It's been so long I've forgotten myself.

00:17:50.708 --> 00:17:52.125
I wonder why...

00:17:52.833 --> 00:17:58.667
When I began developing the full-dive
environment system... No, long before that,

00:17:58.667 --> 00:18:04.500
creating that castle, a world that surpassed
all our laws and all our restrictions,

00:18:04.500 --> 00:18:07.208
was my only desire
and what I lived for.

00:18:08.875 --> 00:18:14.792
And now I've been able to see something
that surpassed my own world's laws...

00:18:17.333 --> 00:18:23.542
How old was I, when I was obsessed with the
fantasy of a steel castle that floated in the sky?

00:18:24.875 --> 00:18:27.083
I wanted to leave the ground

00:18:27.083 --> 00:18:28.833
to fly to that castle.

00:18:29.167 --> 00:18:34.167
For a long, long time,
that was my only desire...

00:18:37.375 --> 00:18:39.167
You know, Kirito,

00:18:39.833 --> 00:18:41.625
I believe even now

00:18:42.292 --> 00:18:46.917
that in some other world,
that castle truly exists.

00:18:49.042 --> 00:18:52.000
Yes... I hope you're right.

00:18:58.333 --> 00:18:59.792
I forgot to tell you something.

00:19:00.375 --> 00:19:04.500
Congratulations on clearing
the game, Kirito, Asuna.

00:19:08.042 --> 00:19:11.167
Now then, I must be going.

00:19:30.750 --> 00:19:32.083
I guess this is goodbye...

00:19:32.958 --> 00:19:34.167
No...

00:19:34.167 --> 00:19:35.625
This isn't goodbye.

00:19:36.167 --> 00:19:38.833
We're going to disappear as one.

00:19:39.458 --> 00:19:41.375
So we'll be together forever.

00:19:42.333 --> 00:19:44.917
Before we do, tell me your name.

00:19:45.208 --> 00:19:47.167
Your real name, Kirito.

00:19:50.375 --> 00:19:53.208
Kirigaya. Kazuto Kirigaya.

00:19:53.208 --> 00:19:55.708
I think I turned 16 last month.

00:19:55.958 --> 00:19:58.500
Kazuto Kirigaya...

00:19:59.750 --> 00:20:01.583
So you're younger than me?

00:20:02.458 --> 00:20:05.125
My name is Asuna Yuki.

00:20:05.458 --> 00:20:06.792
I'm 17.

00:20:07.042 --> 00:20:09.333
Asuna Yuki...

00:20:10.000 --> 00:20:11.667
Asuna Yuki.

00:20:18.875 --> 00:20:21.458
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

00:20:21.458 --> 00:20:26.333
I promised to send you back
to the other world...

00:20:26.750 --> 00:20:29.833
But I... I...

00:20:33.042 --> 00:20:34.167
It's okay.

00:20:35.125 --> 00:20:36.458
It's okay.

00:20:37.000 --> 00:20:41.208
I'm happy I was able to
meet you, Kazuto...

00:20:41.208 --> 00:20:42.708
To live with you.

00:20:43.250 --> 00:20:45.958
This is the happiest
I've ever been in my life.

00:20:46.667 --> 00:20:47.792
Thank you.

00:20:48.250 --> 00:20:49.708
I love you.

00:21:09.250 --> 00:21:10.375
I love...

00:21:11.125 --> 00:21:12.542
I love you.

00:22:15.542 --> 00:22:19.792
A... su... na...

00:22:26.375 --> 00:22:28.792
Asuna...

00:22:30.125 --> 00:22:41.583
<i>The tolling of the faraway bells</i>
<i>sounded a little lonely to me</i>

00:22:41.917 --> 00:22:53.458
<i>So I tried harder, one more time,</i>
<i>this time soaring higher, all the way up</i>

00:22:53.875 --> 00:22:59.417
<i>Neither this reality that just keeps repeating itself</i>

00:22:59.750 --> 00:23:05.208
<i>Nor all my wishes, as numerous as the stars</i>

00:23:05.625 --> 00:23:10.625
<i>Now that I've found the tomorrow</i>
<i>I should strive for</i>

00:23:10.958 --> 00:23:15.917
<i>None of them can overcome these feelings of mine</i>

00:23:16.250 --> 00:23:22.708
<i>A world without end, opening up before my eyes</i>

00:23:23.042 --> 00:23:26.667
<i>Even if it's no more than a dream</i>

00:23:27.250 --> 00:23:34.000
<i>Even if I'm still lost, deep in my heart, it is strong</i>

00:23:34.333 --> 00:23:39.792
<i>Echoing forever and ever</i>

00:23:40.125 --> 00:23:46.292
<i>Shining softly, ever so softly</i>

00:23:47.083 --> 00:23:53.195
Next Time: "Return."
